[
  {
    "startTime": 12.902,
    "endTime": 16.985,
    "text": "I come to you today to speak of liars,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 17.9,
    "endTime": 18.432,
    "text": "lawsuits"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 18.456,
    "endTime": 19.796,
    "text": "and laughter."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 20.73,
    "endTime": 23.84,
    "text": "The first time I heard about Holocaust denial,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 23.864,
    "endTime": 25.166,
    "text": "I laughed."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 25.79,
    "endTime": 27.541,
    "text": "Holocaust denial?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 28.7,
    "endTime": 31.436999999999998,
    "text": "The Holocaust which has the dubious distinction"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 31.461,
    "endTime": 35.955,
    "text": "of being the best-documented genocide in the world?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 36.866,
    "endTime": 38.891,
    "text": "Who could believe it didn't happen?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 39.926,
    "endTime": 41.273,
    "text": "Think about it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 42.77,
    "endTime": 44.358000000000004,
    "text": "For deniers to be right,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 44.382,
    "endTime": 46.278,
    "text": "who would have to be wrong?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 46.831,
    "endTime": 49.597,
    "text": "Well, first of all, the victims --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 49.621,
    "endTime": 54.338,
    "text": "the survivors who have told us their harrowing stories."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 55.541,
    "endTime": 57.855,
    "text": "Who else would have to be wrong?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 57.879,
    "endTime": 59.832,
    "text": "The bystanders."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 59.856,
    "endTime": 63.834,
    "text": "The people who lived in the myriads of towns and villages and cities"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 63.858,
    "endTime": 65.83,
    "text": "on the Eastern front,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 65.854,
    "endTime": 68.295,
    "text": "who watched their neighbors be rounded up --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 68.32,
    "endTime": 71.532,
    "text": "men, women, children, young, old --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 71.557,
    "endTime": 74.277,
    "text": "and be marched to the outskirts of the town"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 74.301,
    "endTime": 77.293,
    "text": "to be shot and left dead in ditches."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 77.805,
    "endTime": 79.135,
    "text": "Or the Poles,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 79.159,
    "endTime": 83.84,
    "text": "who lived in towns and villages around the death camps,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 83.864,
    "endTime": 86.24000000000001,
    "text": "who watched day after day"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 86.264,
    "endTime": 89.6,
    "text": "as the trains went in filled with people"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 89.3,
    "endTime": 90.553,
    "text": "and came out empty."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 91.607,
    "endTime": 95.24,
    "text": "But above all, who would have to be wrong?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 95.825,
    "endTime": 97.289,
    "text": "The perpetrators."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 97.932,
    "endTime": 100.83800000000001,
    "text": "The people who say, \"We did it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 101.299,
    "endTime": 102.82300000000001,
    "text": "I did it.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 102.847,
    "endTime": 104.996,
    "text": "Now, maybe they add a caveat."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 105.2,
    "endTime": 109.444,
    "text": "They say, \"I didn't have a choice; I was forced to do it.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 109.924,
    "endTime": 112.593,
    "text": "But nonetheless, they say, \"I did it.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 113.758,
    "endTime": 115.309,
    "text": "Think about it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 115.333,
    "endTime": 121.271,
    "text": "In not one war crimes trial since the end of World War II"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 121.296,
    "endTime": 127.932,
    "text": "has a perpetrator of any nationality ever said, \"It didn't happen.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 128.898,
    "endTime": 133.48,
    "text": "Again, they may have said, \"I was forced,\" but never that it didn't happen."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 133.504,
    "endTime": 134.977,
    "text": "Having thought that through,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 135.2,
    "endTime": 138.95299999999997,
    "text": "I decided denial was not going to be on my agenda;"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 138.977,
    "endTime": 142.685,
    "text": "I had bigger things to worry about, to write about, to research,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 142.709,
    "endTime": 144.23,
    "text": "and I moved on."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 144.731,
    "endTime": 147.549,
    "text": "Fast-forward a little over a decade,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 147.574,
    "endTime": 149.38600000000002,
    "text": "and two senior scholars --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 149.41,
    "endTime": 152.567,
    "text": "two of the most prominent historians of the Holocaust --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 152.592,
    "endTime": 153.84900000000002,
    "text": "approached me and said,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 153.873,
    "endTime": 155.661,
    "text": "\"Deborah, let's have coffee."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 155.686,
    "endTime": 159.28300000000002,
    "text": "We have a research idea that we think is perfect for you.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 159.307,
    "endTime": 163.14,
    "text": "Intrigued and flattered that they came to me with an idea"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 163.164,
    "endTime": 164.74099999999999,
    "text": "and thought me worthy of it,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 164.765,
    "endTime": 166.861,
    "text": "I asked, \"What is it?\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 167.485,
    "endTime": 170.47400000000002,
    "text": "And they said, \"Holocaust denial.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 171.173,
    "endTime": 173.668,
    "text": "And for the second time, I laughed."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 174.156,
    "endTime": 176.8,
    "text": "Holocaust denial?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 176.104,
    "endTime": 178.9,
    "text": "The Flat Earth folks?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 178.114,
    "endTime": 180.251,
    "text": "The Elvis-is-alive people?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 180.275,
    "endTime": 182.463,
    "text": "I should study them?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 183.146,
    "endTime": 184.463,
    "text": "And these two guys said,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 184.487,
    "endTime": 186.42,
    "text": "\"Yeah, we're intrigued."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 186.832,
    "endTime": 188.404,
    "text": "What are they about?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 188.428,
    "endTime": 190.178,
    "text": "What's their objective?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 190.202,
    "endTime": 193.856,
    "text": "How do they manage to get people to believe what they say?\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 194.576,
    "endTime": 198.10299999999998,
    "text": "So thinking, if they thought it was worthwhile,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 198.128,
    "endTime": 201.50099999999998,
    "text": "I would take a momentary diversion --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 201.526,
    "endTime": 204.464,
    "text": "maybe a year, maybe two, three, maybe even four --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 204.488,
    "endTime": 206.733,
    "text": "in academic terms, that's momentary."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 206.757,
    "endTime": 207.899,
    "text": "(Laughter)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 207.923,
    "endTime": 210.31,
    "text": "We work very slowly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 210.334,
    "endTime": 211.906,
    "text": "(Laughter)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 211.93,
    "endTime": 213.732,
    "text": "And I would look at them."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 213.756,
    "endTime": 214.911,
    "text": "So I did."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 214.935,
    "endTime": 217.774,
    "text": "I did my research, and I came up with a number of things,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 217.798,
    "endTime": 220.391,
    "text": "two of which I'd like to share with you today."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 220.415,
    "endTime": 221.748,
    "text": "One:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 221.772,
    "endTime": 226.72799999999998,
    "text": "deniers are wolves in sheep's clothing."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 227.532,
    "endTime": 230.497,
    "text": "They are the same: Nazis, neo-Nazis --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 230.521,
    "endTime": 233.748,
    "text": "you can decide whether you want to put a \"neo\" there or not."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 234.606,
    "endTime": 236.939,
    "text": "But when I looked at them,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 236.963,
    "endTime": 241.689,
    "text": "I didn't see any SS-like uniforms,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 241.713,
    "endTime": 244.864,
    "text": "swastika-like symbols on the wall,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 244.888,
    "endTime": 246.945,
    "text": "Sieg Heil salutes --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 246.969,
    "endTime": 248.513,
    "text": "none of that."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 248.537,
    "endTime": 251.407,
    "text": "What I found instead"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 251.431,
    "endTime": 256.46000000000004,
    "text": "were people parading as respectable academics."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 256.736,
    "endTime": 257.957,
    "text": "What did they have?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 257.981,
    "endTime": 259.678,
    "text": "They had an institute."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 259.702,
    "endTime": 263.546,
    "text": "An \"Institute for Historical Review.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 264.212,
    "endTime": 266.765,
    "text": "They had a journal -- a slick journal --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 266.79,
    "endTime": 269.744,
    "text": "a \"Journal of Historical Review.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 270.218,
    "endTime": 272.92400000000004,
    "text": "One filled with papers --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 272.948,
    "endTime": 274.991,
    "text": "footnote-laden papers."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 275.743,
    "endTime": 277.683,
    "text": "And they had a new name."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 278.32,
    "endTime": 280.488,
    "text": "Not neo-Nazis,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 280.512,
    "endTime": 283.2,
    "text": "not anti-Semites --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 283.26,
    "endTime": 284.284,
    "text": "revisionists."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 284.811,
    "endTime": 287.25,
    "text": "They said, \"We are revisionists."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 287.5,
    "endTime": 289.733,
    "text": "We are out to do one thing:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 289.757,
    "endTime": 293.317,
    "text": "to revise mistakes in history.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 294.189,
    "endTime": 299.59900000000005,
    "text": "But all you had to do was go one inch below the surface,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 299.623,
    "endTime": 301.53,
    "text": "and what did you find there?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 301.554,
    "endTime": 304.44,
    "text": "The same adulation of Hitler,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 304.68,
    "endTime": 305.943,
    "text": "praise of the Third Reich,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 305.967,
    "endTime": 308.909,
    "text": "anti-Semitism, racism, prejudice."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 309.724,
    "endTime": 312.17,
    "text": "This is what intrigued me."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 312.194,
    "endTime": 319.19100000000003,
    "text": "It was anti-Semitism, racism, prejudice, parading as rational discourse."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 320.55,
    "endTime": 322.137,
    "text": "The other thing I found --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 322.161,
    "endTime": 325.906,
    "text": "many of us have been taught to think there are facts and there are opinions --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 325.93,
    "endTime": 327.386,
    "text": "after studying deniers,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 327.41,
    "endTime": 328.74600000000004,
    "text": "I think differently."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 329.258,
    "endTime": 330.906,
    "text": "There are facts,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 330.93,
    "endTime": 332.644,
    "text": "there are opinions,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 332.668,
    "endTime": 334.28000000000003,
    "text": "and there are lies."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 334.969,
    "endTime": 339.395,
    "text": "And what deniers want to do is take their lies,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 340.385,
    "endTime": 342.17,
    "text": "dress them up as opinions --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 342.41,
    "endTime": 344.31,
    "text": "maybe edgy opinions,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 344.55,
    "endTime": 346.764,
    "text": "maybe sort of out-of-the-box opinions --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 346.788,
    "endTime": 348.172,
    "text": "but then if they're opinions,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 348.196,
    "endTime": 350.32800000000003,
    "text": "they should be part of the conversation."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 350.352,
    "endTime": 353.74399999999997,
    "text": "And then they encroach on the facts."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 355.125,
    "endTime": 356.688,
    "text": "I published my work --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 356.712,
    "endTime": 357.885,
    "text": "the book was published,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 357.91,
    "endTime": 361.312,
    "text": "\"Denying the Holocaust: The Growing Assault on Truth and Memory,\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 361.336,
    "endTime": 363.29200000000003,
    "text": "it came out in many different countries,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 363.316,
    "endTime": 365.476,
    "text": "including here in Penguin UK,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 365.5,
    "endTime": 368.93,
    "text": "and I was done with those folks and ready to move on."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 369.983,
    "endTime": 373.69100000000003,
    "text": "Then came the letter from Penguin UK."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 374.254,
    "endTime": 377.22,
    "text": "And for the third time, I laughed ..."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 378.908,
    "endTime": 380.148,
    "text": "mistakenly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 380.792,
    "endTime": 382.522,
    "text": "I opened the letter,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 382.546,
    "endTime": 388.433,
    "text": "and it informed me that David Irving was bringing a libel suit against me"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 388.458,
    "endTime": 390.55,
    "text": "in the United Kingdom"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 390.79,
    "endTime": 393.115,
    "text": "for calling him a Holocaust denier."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 393.773,
    "endTime": 395.70700000000005,
    "text": "David Irving suing me?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 395.731,
    "endTime": 396.935,
    "text": "Who was David Irving?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 396.959,
    "endTime": 399.56600000000003,
    "text": "David Irving was a writer of historical works,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 399.59,
    "endTime": 401.613,
    "text": "most of them about World War II,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 401.637,
    "endTime": 404.856,
    "text": "and virtually all of those works took the position"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 404.88,
    "endTime": 408.457,
    "text": "that the Nazis were really not so bad,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 408.482,
    "endTime": 411.56600000000003,
    "text": "and the Allies were really not so good."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 411.59,
    "endTime": 413.695,
    "text": "And the Jews, whatever happened to them,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 413.719,
    "endTime": 415.29,
    "text": "they sort of deserved it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 416.26,
    "endTime": 417.517,
    "text": "He knew the documents,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 417.541,
    "endTime": 418.984,
    "text": "he knew the facts,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 419.8,
    "endTime": 422.18,
    "text": "but he somehow twisted them to get this opinion."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 422.836,
    "endTime": 425.348,
    "text": "He hadn't always been a Holocaust denier,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 425.372,
    "endTime": 427.113,
    "text": "but in the late '80s,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 427.137,
    "endTime": 429.564,
    "text": "he embraced it with great vigor."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 431.337,
    "endTime": 435.241,
    "text": "The reason I laughed also was this was a man"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 435.266,
    "endTime": 437.20000000000005,
    "text": "who not only was a Holocaust denier,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 437.224,
    "endTime": 438.919,
    "text": "but seemed quite proud of it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 438.943,
    "endTime": 440.567,
    "text": "Here was a man -- and I quote --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 440.591,
    "endTime": 444.285,
    "text": "who said, \"I'm going to sink the battleship Auschwitz.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 445.165,
    "endTime": 446.33700000000005,
    "text": "Here was a man"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 446.361,
    "endTime": 450.381,
    "text": "who pointed to the number tattooed on a survivor's arm and said,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 451.536,
    "endTime": 453.128,
    "text": "\"How much money have you made"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 453.152,
    "endTime": 456.551,
    "text": "from having that number tattooed on your arm?\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 457.369,
    "endTime": 459.27700000000004,
    "text": "Here was a man who said,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 459.301,
    "endTime": 462.257,
    "text": "\"More people died in Senator Kennedy's car"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 462.281,
    "endTime": 463.593,
    "text": "at Chappaquiddick"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 463.617,
    "endTime": 466.93100000000004,
    "text": "than died in gas chambers at Auschwitz.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 466.955,
    "endTime": 469.792,
    "text": "That's an American reference, but you can look it up."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 471.226,
    "endTime": 474.24,
    "text": "This was not a man who seemed at all ashamed or reticent"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 474.264,
    "endTime": 476.333,
    "text": "about being a Holocaust denier."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 476.956,
    "endTime": 480.736,
    "text": "Now, lots of my academic colleagues counseled me --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 480.76,
    "endTime": 482.666,
    "text": "\"Eh, Deborah, just ignore it.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 482.69,
    "endTime": 486.278,
    "text": "When I explained you can't just ignore a libel suit,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 486.302,
    "endTime": 489.84000000000003,
    "text": "they said, \"Who's going to believe him anyway?\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 489.603,
    "endTime": 491.683,
    "text": "But here was the problem:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 491.707,
    "endTime": 497.15,
    "text": "British law put the onus, put the burden of proof on me"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 497.39,
    "endTime": 499.721,
    "text": "to prove the truth of what I said,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 499.745,
    "endTime": 502.508,
    "text": "in contrast to as it would have been in the United States"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 502.532,
    "endTime": 504.35999999999996,
    "text": "and in many other countries:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 504.6,
    "endTime": 507.66,
    "text": "on him to prove the falsehood."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 507.741,
    "endTime": 509.202,
    "text": "What did that mean?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 509.226,
    "endTime": 512.602,
    "text": "That meant if I didn't fight,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 512.626,
    "endTime": 515.52,
    "text": "he would win by default."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 515.611,
    "endTime": 517.366,
    "text": "And if he won by default,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 517.39,
    "endTime": 520.3,
    "text": "he could then legitimately say,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 520.54,
    "endTime": 525.391,
    "text": "\"My David Irving version of the Holocaust is a legitimate version."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 525.415,
    "endTime": 527.598,
    "text": "Deborah Lipstadt was found to have libeled me"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 527.623,
    "endTime": 529.57,
    "text": "when she called me a Holocaust denier."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 529.594,
    "endTime": 534.22,
    "text": "Ipso facto, I, David Irving, am not a Holocaust denier.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 534.46,
    "endTime": 535.758,
    "text": "And what is that version?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 536.251,
    "endTime": 539.247,
    "text": "There was no plan to murder the Jews,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 539.271,
    "endTime": 541.323,
    "text": "there were no gas chambers,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 541.347,
    "endTime": 543.203,
    "text": "there were no mass shootings,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 543.227,
    "endTime": 546.398,
    "text": "Hitler had nothing to do with any suffering that went on,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 546.422,
    "endTime": 550.227,
    "text": "and the Jews have made this all up"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 550.251,
    "endTime": 552.649,
    "text": "to get money from Germany"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 552.673,
    "endTime": 554.38,
    "text": "and to get a state,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 554.404,
    "endTime": 557.781,
    "text": "and they've done it with the aid and abettance of the Allies --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 557.805,
    "endTime": 561.27,
    "text": "they've planted the documents and planted the evidence."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 562.28,
    "endTime": 564.66,
    "text": "I couldn't let that stand"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 564.684,
    "endTime": 566.884,
    "text": "and ever face a survivor"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 567.643,
    "endTime": 569.618,
    "text": "or a child of survivors."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 569.642,
    "endTime": 571.7940000000001,
    "text": "I couldn't let that stand"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 571.818,
    "endTime": 576.6899999999999,
    "text": "and consider myself a responsible historian."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 577.7,
    "endTime": 578.7520000000001,
    "text": "So we fought."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 578.776,
    "endTime": 581.5799999999999,
    "text": "And for those of you who haven't seen \"Denial,\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 581.82,
    "endTime": 582.2410000000001,
    "text": "spoiler alert:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 582.265,
    "endTime": 583.483,
    "text": "we won."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 583.507,
    "endTime": 584.8009999999999,
    "text": "(Laughter)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 584.826,
    "endTime": 587.393,
    "text": "(Applause)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 591.808,
    "endTime": 596.49,
    "text": "The judge found David Irving"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 596.73,
    "endTime": 599.404,
    "text": "to be a liar,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 599.428,
    "endTime": 600.591,
    "text": "a racist,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 600.615,
    "endTime": 601.869,
    "text": "an anti-Semite."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 601.893,
    "endTime": 604.253,
    "text": "His view of history was tendentious,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 604.277,
    "endTime": 606.2030000000001,
    "text": "he lied, he distorted --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 606.227,
    "endTime": 608.87,
    "text": "and most importantly,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 608.894,
    "endTime": 611.7,
    "text": "he did it deliberately."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 611.31,
    "endTime": 615.17,
    "text": "We showed a pattern, in over 25 different major instances."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 615.194,
    "endTime": 618.304,
    "text": "Not small things -- many of us in this audience write books,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 618.328,
    "endTime": 619.512,
    "text": "are writing books;"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 619.537,
    "endTime": 623.3000000000001,
    "text": "we always make mistakes, that's why we're glad to have second editions:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 623.27,
    "endTime": 624.213,
    "text": "correct the mistakes."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 624.237,
    "endTime": 625.387,
    "text": "(Laughter)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 626.454,
    "endTime": 629.5889999999999,
    "text": "But these always moved in the same direction:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 630.438,
    "endTime": 632.649,
    "text": "blame the Jews,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 632.673,
    "endTime": 634.848,
    "text": "exonerate the Nazis."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 635.52,
    "endTime": 637.103,
    "text": "But how did we win?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 638.16,
    "endTime": 643.396,
    "text": "What we did is follow his footnotes back to his sources."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 644.1,
    "endTime": 645.793,
    "text": "And what did we find?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 645.817,
    "endTime": 647.296,
    "text": "Not in most cases,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 647.32,
    "endTime": 649.288,
    "text": "and not in the preponderance of cases,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 649.312,
    "endTime": 653.623,
    "text": "but in every single instance where he made some reference to the Holocaust,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 653.647,
    "endTime": 657.889,
    "text": "that his supposed evidence was distorted,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 657.913,
    "endTime": 659.333,
    "text": "half-truth,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 659.357,
    "endTime": 660.6899999999999,
    "text": "date-changed,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 660.715,
    "endTime": 662.902,
    "text": "sequence-changed,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 662.926,
    "endTime": 665.5,
    "text": "someone put at a meeting who wasn't there."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 665.74,
    "endTime": 667.8340000000001,
    "text": "In other words, he didn't have the evidence."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 667.859,
    "endTime": 669.9680000000001,
    "text": "His evidence didn't prove it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 669.992,
    "endTime": 672.651,
    "text": "We didn't prove what happened."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 673.448,
    "endTime": 675.947,
    "text": "We proved that what he said happened --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 675.971,
    "endTime": 678.831,
    "text": "and by extension, all deniers, because he either quotes them"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 678.855,
    "endTime": 681.326,
    "text": "or they get their arguments from him --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 681.35,
    "endTime": 682.596,
    "text": "is not true."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 682.62,
    "endTime": 683.809,
    "text": "What they claim --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 683.833,
    "endTime": 686.454,
    "text": "they don't have the evidence to prove it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 688.429,
    "endTime": 693.173,
    "text": "So why is my story more than just the story"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 693.197,
    "endTime": 697.4,
    "text": "of a quirky, long, six-year, difficult lawsuit,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 697.28,
    "endTime": 702.17,
    "text": "an American professor being dragged into a courtroom"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 702.41,
    "endTime": 705.85,
    "text": "by a man that the court declared in its judgment"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 705.109,
    "endTime": 707.359,
    "text": "was a neo-Nazi polemicist?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 707.383,
    "endTime": 709.166,
    "text": "What message does it have?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 709.62,
    "endTime": 712.593,
    "text": "I think in the context of the question of truth,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 712.617,
    "endTime": 715.79,
    "text": "it has a very significant message."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 715.103,
    "endTime": 716.887,
    "text": "Because today,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 716.912,
    "endTime": 718.5780000000001,
    "text": "as we well know,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 718.602,
    "endTime": 722.718,
    "text": "truth and facts are under assault."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 723.522,
    "endTime": 726.774,
    "text": "Social media, for all the gifts it has given us,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 726.798,
    "endTime": 732.379,
    "text": "has also allowed the difference between facts -- established facts --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 732.403,
    "endTime": 734.16,
    "text": "and lies"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 734.184,
    "endTime": 735.582,
    "text": "to be flattened."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 736.81,
    "endTime": 738.319,
    "text": "Third of all:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 738.344,
    "endTime": 739.815,
    "text": "extremism."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 740.807,
    "endTime": 744.384,
    "text": "You may not see Ku Klux Klan robes,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 744.408,
    "endTime": 746.479,
    "text": "you may not see burning crosses,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 746.503,
    "endTime": 750.822,
    "text": "you may not even hear outright white supremacist language."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 750.846,
    "endTime": 755.752,
    "text": "It may go by names: \"alt-right,\" \"National Front\" -- pick your names."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 755.776,
    "endTime": 761.611,
    "text": "But underneath, it's that same extremism that I found in Holocaust denial"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 761.635,
    "endTime": 765.29,
    "text": "parading as rational discourse."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 766.954,
    "endTime": 772.17,
    "text": "We live in an age where truth is on the defensive."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 772.195,
    "endTime": 774.6790000000001,
    "text": "I'm reminded of a New Yorker cartoon."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 774.703,
    "endTime": 777.223,
    "text": "A quiz show recently appeared in \"The New Yorker\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 777.247,
    "endTime": 780.468,
    "text": "where the host of the quiz show is saying to one of the contestants,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 780.493,
    "endTime": 782.802,
    "text": "\"Yes, ma'am, you had the right answer."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 782.826,
    "endTime": 785.3190000000001,
    "text": "But your opponent yelled more loudly than you did,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 785.343,
    "endTime": 786.867,
    "text": "so he gets the point.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 788.48,
    "endTime": 789.5550000000001,
    "text": "What can we do?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 790.377,
    "endTime": 791.7529999999999,
    "text": "First of all,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 791.778,
    "endTime": 797.2090000000001,
    "text": "we cannot be beguiled by rational appearances."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 797.233,
    "endTime": 799.1999999999999,
    "text": "We've got to look underneath,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 799.26,
    "endTime": 801.827,
    "text": "and we will find there the extremism."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 802.811,
    "endTime": 804.797,
    "text": "Second of all,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 804.821,
    "endTime": 810.902,
    "text": "we must understand that truth is not relative."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 812.957,
    "endTime": 814.421,
    "text": "Number three,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 814.445,
    "endTime": 818.134,
    "text": "we must go on the offensive,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 818.158,
    "endTime": 819.931,
    "text": "not the defensive."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 820.496,
    "endTime": 823.103,
    "text": "When someone makes an outrageous claim,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 823.127,
    "endTime": 826.631,
    "text": "even though they may hold one of the highest offices in the land,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 826.655,
    "endTime": 828.665,
    "text": "if not the world --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 828.69,
    "endTime": 830.2,
    "text": "we must say to them,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 830.224,
    "endTime": 832.19,
    "text": "\"Where's the proof?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 832.214,
    "endTime": 834.351,
    "text": "Where's the evidence?\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 834.375,
    "endTime": 837.302,
    "text": "We must hold their feet to the fire."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 837.326,
    "endTime": 841.932,
    "text": "We must not treat it as if their lies are the same as the facts."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 843.215,
    "endTime": 846.755,
    "text": "And as I said earlier, truth is not relative."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 846.779,
    "endTime": 849.635,
    "text": "Many of us have grown up in the world of the academy"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 849.659,
    "endTime": 851.4,
    "text": "and enlightened liberal thought,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 851.424,
    "endTime": 854.385,
    "text": "where we're taught everything is open to debate."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 854.984,
    "endTime": 856.998,
    "text": "But that's not the case."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 857.22,
    "endTime": 860.464,
    "text": "There are certain things that are true."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 861.12,
    "endTime": 864.3100000000001,
    "text": "There are indisputable facts --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 864.56,
    "endTime": 865.746,
    "text": "objective truths."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 866.339,
    "endTime": 871.1560000000001,
    "text": "Galileo taught it to us centuries ago."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 871.18,
    "endTime": 875.847,
    "text": "Even after being forced to recant by the Vatican"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 875.871,
    "endTime": 878.444,
    "text": "that the Earth moved around the Sun,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 878.468,
    "endTime": 879.622,
    "text": "he came out,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 879.646,
    "endTime": 881.9549999999999,
    "text": "and what is he reported to have said?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 881.98,
    "endTime": 885.802,
    "text": "\"And yet, it still moves.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 887.162,
    "endTime": 890.2,
    "text": "The Earth is not flat."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 890.26,
    "endTime": 892.3149999999999,
    "text": "The climate is changing."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 893.207,
    "endTime": 895.475,
    "text": "Elvis is not alive."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 895.499,
    "endTime": 897.34,
    "text": "(Laughter)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 897.58,
    "endTime": 899.374,
    "text": "(Applause)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 899.398,
    "endTime": 901.6990000000001,
    "text": "And most importantly,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 901.723,
    "endTime": 906.372,
    "text": "truth and fact are under assault."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 907.109,
    "endTime": 908.719,
    "text": "The job ahead of us,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 908.743,
    "endTime": 909.946,
    "text": "the task ahead of us,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 909.97,
    "endTime": 911.5640000000001,
    "text": "the challenge ahead of us"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 911.588,
    "endTime": 912.822,
    "text": "is great."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 913.567,
    "endTime": 916.204,
    "text": "The time to fight is short."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 917.61,
    "endTime": 919.904,
    "text": "We must act now."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 920.749,
    "endTime": 923.994,
    "text": "Later will be too late."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 924.18,
    "endTime": 925.28,
    "text": "Thank you very much."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 925.304,
    "endTime": 929.35,
    "text": "(Applause)"
  }
]